<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="true-adj">true <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /truː/    美 /truː/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>真的；合乎事实的：</strong></h4>
<p>反 untrue / false </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I do not know whether what I’ve been told is <strong>true or false</strong>.
我不知道自己听到的是真还是假。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>His first book to be published next month is based on <strong>a true story</strong>.
他下月出版的第一本书是根据一个真实的故事写的。</p><footer>2010 陕西</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The food in this restaurant is good and <strong>the same is true of</strong> the service.
这家餐馆的饭菜好，服务也好。</p></div>

<h4 id="2-real">2.★ <strong>实际的；真实的 (real)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>True happiness comes from spiritual riches.
真正的幸福来自于精神的富有。</p><footer>2014 福建</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>A smile may show love or politeness. It can also hide <strong>true feelings</strong>.
微笑可以表示爱或礼貌，也能用来掩饰真实的感受。</p><footer>2012 全国</footer></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>真正的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>true love / a true friend
真爱/真正的朋友</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.★ <strong>确实的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>It is true</strong> ( <strong>that</strong> ) you can’t judge a book by its cover.
确实不能以貌取人。</p><footer>2012 陕西改</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="come-true">come true</h3>
<p>1.<strong>实现；成为现实：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>These predictions will come true if technology continues to develop.
如果技术不断发展，这些预言将会成真。</p><footer>外研④ – 1</footer></div></div>